Enum CaseSignificance

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<CaseSignificance>

    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<CaseSignificance>

    public enum CaseSignificance
extends java.lang.Enum<CaseSignificance>
    Enumeration representing a value that can be applied to the SNOMED CT description.

    Available values:

    • Case sensitive
    • Case insensitive
    • Initial character case insensitive

      • ENTIRE_TERM_CASE_SENSITIVE

        public static final CaseSignificance ENTIRE_TERM_CASE_SENSITIVE
        Case sensitive. Concept ID: 900000000000017005.

        The text of the Description.term must be presented in the case in which it is specified.

        See Also:
        CaseSignificance

      • ENTIRE_TERM_CASE_INSENSITIVE

        public static final CaseSignificance ENTIRE_TERM_CASE_INSENSITIVE
        Case insensitive. Concept ID: 900000000000448009.

        The entire Description.term is case insensitive and can be can be changed from upper to lower case (or vice-versa) if appropriate to the context in which it is used.

        See Also:
        CaseSignificance

      • ONLY_INITIAL_CHARACTER_CASE_INSENSITIVE

        public static final CaseSignificance ONLY_INITIAL_CHARACTER_CASE_INSENSITIVE
        Initial character case insensitive. Concept ID: 900000000000020002.

        The initial character of the Description.term is case insensitive and can be changed from upper to lower case (or vice-versa) if appropriate to the context in which it is used.

        See Also:
        CaseSignificance
